title: Grateful Dead Live at Capital Centre on 1992-03-08
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi CR-7A) > Tascam DA-3000 (DSF 1-bit/5.6 MHz) >KORG AudioGate 4 > Samplitude Pro X3 Suite > FLAC/24
description:
Set 1

Let The Good Times Roll, Touch Of Gray, Minglewood Blues, Ramble On Rose, Black Throated Wind, Loose Lucy, Desolation Row, Big Railroad Blues, The Music Never Stopped

Set 2

Samson & Delilah, Way To Go Home, Foolish Heart-> Looks Like Rain, Wave To The Wind-> Jam-> Drums-> Jam-> All Along The Watchtower, So Many Roads, Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away, E: The Mighty Quinn

reviews.review_text: Very good SBD Excellent show! Fades off a bit after drums, but not much.

My 2nd show. In "touch" jerry sez "Say your piece and PISS oFF"  i had to go back and listen twice to verify.

At the time, show seemed rather avg.  I was blown away by rfk 90 and 93, my 1st, 4th and 5th shows.  But for some reason this one didnt grab me.  Maybe lucy didnt hold my hand tight enough or whatever.

I remember in the mezzanine between sets, people were excited about how many songs they played set 1.  Caps Center was a good venue thet seemed to enjoy.

I dunno, im not gonna do my usual intense review of this show unless upon listening to it, i hear something really interesting, in which case i will edit/re-post this review.

Honestly, my friend and i listened to EVERY 92 show last year and took notes and until you get to december when things musically acheive AN ENYIRELY NEW LEVEL OF AWESOMENESS, the only 5 star show in 92 is Charlotte from June.  That show is like, woah, they just clicked x faxtor style.
